Leaked audio just dropped of JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon going on a rant about work from home, and honestly, it’s hilarious. Apparently, if you’re on Zoom, you’re not paying attention, sending memes to your coworkers, and just being a generally useless human being. Meanwhile, JPMorgan’s profits are at record highs, so… which is it, Jamie?

He also claims remote work is ruining young professionals, as if sitting next to Jim from Accounting is some kind of life-changing mentorship. Oh, and the best part? He compares desk jobs to working in a restaurant, because,
